#stance=stance2
#originalStanceText=Yes
#originalTopic=Debate:_DC_handgun_ban
A 2nd Amendment that confers individual rights would be too expansive in limiting government. Oral arguments in DC vs. Heller. March 19th, 2008 - "One of the troublesome aspects of viewing this as a right of personal use is that that is the kind of fundamental liberty interest that would create a real potential for disruption. Once you unmoor it from -- or untether it from its connection to the protection of the State militia, you have the kind of right that could easily be restrictions on State and local governments"...
